{
  "text": "The Markov approximation is obtained, if in equation (2.9) we replace the density matrix\u03c1(s) by\u03c1(\u03c4 ) and take the upper limit to infinity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . We note that the Markov approximation is justified only if the correlation functions of the environment decay very rapidly compared to the timescale on which\u03c1(\u03c4 ) changes. Expressing the density operator in a matrix form",
